The kind of Islam followed in the US is high on rituals but low on spirit. The bigger the Islamic center, the worse the problem is. The core of the problem lies in the boards that manage the affairs at each Islamic center. The people who sit on those boards reach that position not due to their taqwa but due to their worldly affairs. As a result they hire the imams to pursue worldly interests such as connecting with non-Muslims, being open to mixing of sexes in the mosque, being feminist, etc.  And majority of Muslims also prioritize those things. The board decides everything and then uses the imam as a rubber stamp, and if the imam refuses to be a rubber stamp the boards refuse to renew the imam's contract. Since it is much easier to pressurize foreign imams due to their visa tied to their contract, it is far easier for boards to pressurize them. I don't think ability to speak English is such a big problem because most Muslims in the US are bilingual anyway. Also, some of the hardest subjects in US universities are taught by foreign born and raised professors who have bad English. The real issue is the desire of the boards to have puppet imams in the US that ratifies board decisions without question !
